Description:
Classic Terrace with Tremendous Character and Potential
Brilliantly positioned in one of Collingwood's finest tree lined locations you have the golden opportunity to secure this spacious two storey semi-detached terrace on approximately 217sqm parcel of land.
The property has the timeless appeal of original historic character and fine period details, offering a perfectly liveable home as-is with potential to redesign and capitalise in a sought-after location.
A traditional floor plan includes a vast balcony bedroom and three further very spacious bedrooms. All with high ceilings, OFP and hydronic heating. The arched hallway leads to a living-dining room and kitchen with breakfast bar plus rear laundry-bathroom. Delightful large north facing garden with street access.
A fabulous location, it's close to cafes and restaurants,trams and trains to CBD.

Situated For Success
Moments to buzzing Victoria Street and an exceptional range of transport options, this contemporary and secure one bedroom apartment boasts spacious open plan living and dining zones, a quality kitchen overflowing with stainless steel appliances, and a cool paved courtyard where you can chill out and enjoy your hard-earned leisure time.
An easy walk or jog to Fitzroy Gardens, handy to Melbourne's major sporting precinct and so close to the best features the city has to offer, it's an enticing investment or great base for a fashionable urban lifestyle.
The bedroom comes with a mirrored built-in robe, the bathroom handily hosts a European laundry, and extras include split system heating/cooling, a secure entry with intercom, elevator access and basement parking.

Description:
Meticulously updated city fringe apartment with northern sun
Privately elevated in a secure low-rise complex, this wonderfully modern apartment embodies fresh updates, abundant northern sunlight and quality inclusions. The practical layout comprises an open plan design with relaxed living and dining areas. A near new stone-finished kitchen is equipped with stainless appliances and a sun filled urban outlook.
There are two double sized bedrooms complete with built-in wardrobes, including the main bedroom that opens onto a broad balcony setting. Additional highlights include an immaculately renovated bathroom with high-end fittings, fresh and inviting colour palette plus a single secure car space. It presents a rare entry level/investment opportunity for young couples seeking space and style in a sought-after city fringe address.
Perfectly positioned less than 5 kilometres from the heart of Melbourne, this impressive property is only an easy stroll away from Victoria Park Station, Darling Gardens, local shops, cafs, restaurants and the Yarra River.

Description:
Stunning Manhattan-style warehouse apartment in the heart of Collingwood
An innovative fusion of industrial style and cutting-edge functionality, this stunning warehouse apartment occupies a first floor position within the iconic Foy and Gibson factory complex, designed by renowned architect William Pitt in 1887. Capturing Manhattan-style living in the heart of Collingwood, it is defined by luxuriously spacious original proportions and elegantly appointed contemporary interiors with a dynamic street outlook.
An exclusive inner city offering tailored for executive owner-occupiers and savvy investors alike, it is ideally located footsteps from Smith Street cafes and bars, a host of galleries, parks and trams providing a direct CBD commute.
Polished floorboards flow from the wide entrance hall into a huge living and dining area. Set beneath high ceilings with exposed beams, it is flooded in natural light through oversized windows. A smart integrated kitchen completes the superb open plan design. It boasts premium stainless steel appliances including an oven, gas cooktop and Bosch dishwasher, a large breakfast bar and plentiful cabinetry. Nearby is the enormous main bedroom with twin built-in robes, sizeable second bedroom also with twin built-in robes and sparkling bathroom with a shower over a full bath.
Enjoying pedestrian entry via Stanley Street, it features a European laundry, electric heating, brick feature walls, ambient downlighting, minimalist tones and a secure basement car space with storage and lift access. In addition, the impeccably maintained low-rise building has video intercom and a chic polished concrete foyer with a marble staircase.
Anton Wongtrakun : 0419 352 888

Description:
A STUNNING INDUSTRIAL CHIC - WAREHOUSE CONVERSION APARTMENT OVER 2 ATMOSPHERIC LEVELS
This historic and fascinating "Foy and Gibson " industrial woolen mills facade is really only a clever foil for what lies within!
Architect designed with flair and imagination, yet mindful of privacy and security, offering all of the very best elements of New York style warehouse conversion living; such as ample space, good height, plenty of natural light and superb polished concrete floors. This fabulous roomy and airy 2 level apartment is a clever melding of the " old and the new" providing all of todays up-to-the-minute accoutrements including stylish fittings and Euro appliances. It comprises security entry foyer, loads of living, dining and entertaining space, 2 well proportioned bedrooms with built ins, attractive central bathroom, separate downstairs powder room and a huge laundry/auxilliary room, plus secure on-title basement parking and a sizable storage locker.
What an enviable, urban and relaxed lifestyle on offer here, only 2 and a bit kms to the CBD! - Throw away the car keys if you really even need one at all - jump on the tram or even walk to the city or the footy, stroll down to Proud Mary for breakfast or brunch, have a picnic in the little park on the other corner or pop around to the gorgeous "Local", the Grace Darling in Smith Street for one of their famous Sunday roasts or happy hours. Surely this one must tick all your buying boxes!
AUCTION SATURDAY THE 11TH OF OCTOBER AT 12 NOON
Contact BRUCE BAVIN 0410 273 734 FRANK CALLAGHAN 0407 313 753

Description:
Light and Space - the essence of warehouse living
With its spacious floorplan (almost 90sqm), quality features and abundance of natural light, this Manhattan-style apartment offers an outstanding city-edge lifestyle in Collingwood's iconic Foy & Gibson warehouse precinct. Vast interior comprises one large bedroom with robes, huge open-plan living/dining area (with potential for creating a second bedroom), stylish two-way bathroom, study area and superb kitchen with stainless steel appliances. Highlights include polished hardwood floors, towering ceilings, laundry facilities, big storage loft, plus a private foyer with lift access and secure car space. A premier Fitzroy-edge location, it's walking distance to Smith Street shops, cafes and trams.

Description:
Top Of The Class!
Located in the former Foy & Gibson 'New York on Oxford' Heritage listed building - this trendy warehouse apartment is impressive with its unique design and spacious floor plan. Opportunity presents to live in a modern apartment with real warehouse charm where key features including exposed brick, beams and high ceilings have been retained. It offers immediate comfort as well as additional scope to further enhance. Comprises three huge bedrooms, 2 with en-suites, plus study, open plan living, contemporary kitchen, powder room and European laundry. Other features include: heating, dishwasher, plenty of storage and secured car space.
Walking distance to all key amenities, including public transport, cafes and shops. Metres away from Smith, Gertrude, Brunswick & Victoria Streets with CBD, MCG & more just on the doorstep. Call Today!
